.\" Wawona apt — App Store module compatibility layer
.TH APT 8 "2026" "Wawona" "Wawona App Store modules"
.SH NAME
apt \- manage App Store\-approved Wawona modules
.SH DESCRIPTION
The \fBapt\fR command is a compatibility layer for installing and removing
Wawona modules that have been reviewed and approved for the App Store.
It is not a general\-purpose package manager.
.PP
Modules are listed in an embedded catalog. Installation uses StoreKit
authorization and On\-Demand Resources hosted by Apple. Users cannot add
third\-party repositories or install user\-supplied binaries.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-version\fR
Print Wawona apt identity. This is not Debian APT and has no standalone package
version. Describes the App Store module approach and backends used.
.TP
\fB\-\-about\fR
Print App Store compliance summary.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
\fBapt search\fR [\fIpattern\fR]
Search the approved module catalog.
.TP
\fBapt install\fR \fImodule\fR
Install an approved module.
.TP
\fBapt remove\fR \fImodule\fR
Remove a locally installed module.
.TP
\fBapt list\fR [\fB\-\-installed\fR]
List catalog entries or installed modules.
.TP
\fBapt show\fR \fImodule\fR
Display module metadata.
.TP
\fBapt \-\-about\fR
Print compliance summary.
.SH SEE ALSO
Wawona documentation: wwn\-apt/docs/APP\-STORE\-MODULES.md
